  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/business/\u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dad\u0dca-\u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0daf-\u0daf\u0dd6\u0dad-\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0d9a\u0dca-\u0dc4\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda-\u0db4\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dab\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda-\u0d87\u0dba\u0dd2-/7-394809",
  "time_ut": 1656134603,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dad\u0dca \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0daf \u0daf\u0dd6\u0dad \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc4\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0db4\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dab\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0d87\u0dba\u0dd2?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Why is a US delegation suddenly arriving?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The US Embassy in Sri Lanka announces that a high-level delegation representing the US Treasury Department and the US State Department will visit Sri Lanka from June 26 to 29.",
        "Members of the delegation include Deputy Assistant Treasury Secretary for Asia Robert Kaproth and Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for South and Central Asia Kelly Keiderlin.",
        "During their stay in Sri Lanka, they are also expected to meet a wide range of political representatives, economic experts and international organizations.",
        "At all of those meetings, the delegation will work to explore the most effective ways the United States can provide support to Sri Lankans in need, Sri Lankans working to resolve the current economic crisis, and Sri Lankans planning a sustainable and inclusive economy for the future. The embassy says.",
        "\"This visit demonstrates our continued commitment to the safety and well-being of the Sri Lankan people.\" Says Julie Chung, US Ambassador to Sri Lanka. \"At a time when Sri Lankans are facing some of the most serious economic challenges in their history, our efforts to support Sri Lanka's economic growth and strengthen the country's democratic institutions are more important than ever.\"",
        "In the past fortnight, USD 120 million in new financing for Sri Lankan SMEs, USD 27 million in aid to Sri Lanka's dairy industry, and USD 100 million in humanitarian aid to help those hardest hit by the economic crisis. The United States announced that it will also provide 5.75 million. Also, the United States has announced $6 million in new grants to provide livelihood support to vulnerable populations and provide technical assistance for financial reforms to stabilize the economy.",
        "As Sri Lankans rebuild their economy, combat food insecurity, and promote health and education in the coming months, the United States will continue to support Sri Lanka, the embassy said. The embassy further emphasizes that the United States strongly supports Sri Lanka's decision to seek assistance from the International Monetary Fund, which can provide the most lasting solution to the current crisis."
      ],
